        <h1 class="w-full mb-4 font-serif text-4xl font-bold uppercase sm:w-auto sm:text-5xl text-oak sm:mb-0">
          The Pawn
        </h1>
        <hr class="w-4/5 mx-auto border-2 sm:w-auto sm:flex-1 border-oak sm:mx-0">
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-lg">
        <p>
          The pawn is the most numerous and low-value piece in chess, capable of advancing forward and capturing
          diagonally. It represents the backbone of a player's position and is essential for controlling the board.
        </p>
        <p>
          The pawn is most effective when it is supported by other pieces, creating a strong formation that can control
          key squares. Players must be mindful of pawn structure and potential weaknesses, as isolated or doubled
          pawns can become targets for attack.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
