        data-piece="pawn" data-type="movements"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full lg:w-7/12 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-center uppercase sm:text-left sm:text-4xl text-oak">
          How It Moves
        </h2>
        <hr class="w-4/5 mx-auto border-2 sm:w-full lg:w-4/5 border-oak sm:mx-0">
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-center sm:text-left">
        <p>
          The pawn moves forward one square, but captures diagonally. This unique movement allows it to control key
          squares and create threats.
        </p>
        <p>
          Pawns can only move two squares forward on their first move, providing an opportunity for rapid advancement.
          However, this can also lead to overextension and vulnerability.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

